OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Marion
OL,4,CLoveland
OL,6,F"I remember going for breakfast in the
OL,7,Fwardroom and hearing on the radio that
OL,8,Fwe had invaded.
OL,10,F"Then gradually bits and pieces of
OL,11,Fnews of how things had gone, they
OL,12,Fbecame evident."
OL,14,FLater when she was working for an oil
OL,15,Fcompany Mrs Loveland began
OL,16,Fcorresponding with a man who had
OL,17,Fserved in Burma during the war.
OL,19,FShe said: "When he came home he asked
OL,20,Fto meet me and we got on very well. We
OL,21,Fhad a very good life."
